      • setHitbox

        void setHitbox(IHitbox value)
        Sets the hitbox of this entity. This can be used to change the apparent 'size' of the entity's click boundary. Changing this to a smaller box will result in the original area of the large box being a dead zone, where clicking does nothing. When changing to a larger box, the new area can only be interacted with by using the attack action.
        Hitboxes can be generated through the IFakeEntityFactory interface. An instance of this factory should be obtained from the IPacketEntityAPI root instance.
        Parameters:
        value - the new hitbox to use for this entity

      • getIdentifier

        IEntityIdentifier getIdentifier()
        Gets the identifier of this entity. Use this identifier when spawning packets through a IEntityPacketFactory. An instance of this factory should be obtained from the IPacketEntityAPI root instance.
        Returns:
        the identifier that corresponds to this entity

      • getModifiableEntity

        IModifiableEntity getModifiableEntity()
        Gets the modifiable entity that is tied to this entity. Use this in coordination with IEntityModifiers to change entity metadata - such as name, invisibility, size, color, etc. Modifier instances should be obtained from the IEntityModifierRegistry, which is obtained from the IPacketEntityAPI root instance. Note: these modifiers should be CACHED.
        Modifers can also be obtained from getModifiers().
        Returns:
        the modifiable entity reference that is tied to this entity

      • checkIntersect

        boolean checkIntersect(org.bukkit.entity.Player target)
        Checks whether or not the Player provided is intersecting the fake entity. This is used by the PacketEntityAPI engine to allow for the clicking of fake entities. To override the function used to check this, see setCheckIntersect(BiFunction)
        Parameters:
        target - the player to test
        Returns:
        whether or not the player is intersecting the fake entity

      • getField

        Object getField(String name)
        Gets a parameter that has been previously set for the spawning of this object. For examples of titles, see #setField.
        You can also store custom data in here.
        Parameters:
        name - a string identifier for the parameter
        Returns:
        the defined value of the field

      • setField

        void setField(String name,
              Object value)
        Sets a parameter that is used in the spawning of this object. For example:
        "title" - The Art that should be shown on a painting.
        "direction" - A BlockFace that provides the direction of a painting or item frame.
        "orbcount" - The integer number of experience that an orb is worth.
        "velocity" - The velocity to spawn the object with.
        "shooter" - The integer Entity ID of the person who fired this fake entity.
        "id" - The type ID of the falling block's appearance.
        "data" - The data value of the falling block's appearance.
        You can also store custom data in here.
        Parameters:
        name - a name of a parameter given above
        value - the value to set it to

      • hasField

        Returns:
        whether or not the parameter was found
